<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-251] Generalize Dirichlet models and model distributions to handle n-d and sparse vectors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-251</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Users attempting to use Dirichlet Process Clustering on real life problems cannot use any of the existing models or model distributions as these have hard-coded assumptions of a 2-d DenseVector underlying data representation. These limitations are overly restrictive and the code needs to be generatlized.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
